21-22 January - Ricotta Pie

Filling
- 2 lb ricotta cheese
- 1 teaspoon vanilla
- 1 cup sugar
- 4 egg whites
- 2 small chocolate bars with almonds

Dough
- 2 1/2 cup flour
- 1/2   cup sugar
- 1/4   cup milk
- 1 1/2 teaspoon baking powder
- 2     tablespoon shortening
- 4     egg yolks 

Topping
- 1 egg yolk
- cinnamon
- confectioners sugar

Mix all filling ingredients together and set aside. 

Make a soft crust dough, split in half and roll each piece 1/4" thick. Put half in a deep dish pie plate. Add the filling and put another layer of crust on top. Spread egg yolk over the entire pie and sprinkle with cinnamon. Bake at 375F until crust is lightly browned. Lower oven to 200F and bake one hour. When done dust with confectioners sugar. 